  "text": "Electron microscopic analysis of thin sections of BTV- Bitew et al. 5775 infected cells have revealed a large number of virusspecific tubules (52.3 nm diameter and 1000 nm long) composed of multimers of the NS1 protein, a striking intracellular morphological feature of BTV infection. NS1 has a role in BTV cytopathogenesis [CITATION_1] .",
